---
const categories = {
    device: [
        { title: 'mobile', description: 'designed for the era of ubiquitous computing. these wallets embody the principle of financial freedom - your money, always at your fingertips.' },
        { title: 'desktop', description: 'offering a balance between security and usability. ideal for those who prefer to manage their finances from a dedicated machine.' },
        { title: 'web', description: 'while convenient, these represent a trade-off in the core principle of decentralization. use with caution.' },
        { title: 'hardware', description: 'the epitome of security in the digital age. these devices bridge the gap between the intangible nature of bitcoin and the physical world.' }
    ],
    autonomy: [
        { title: 'full node', description: 'the backbone of the bitcoin network. by running a full node, you\'re not just using bitcoin; you\'re actively participating in its consensus and security.' },
        { title: 'lightweight (spv)', description: 'a compromise between full autonomy and practicality. these clients verify transactions without the full burden of the blockchain.' },
        { title: 'third-party api', description: 'while convenient, these solutions introduce trust, which goes against bitcoin\'s trustless nature. use them understanding the trade-offs.' }
    ],
    custody: [
        { title: 'non-custodial', description: 'the true embodiment of "be your own bank". with great power comes great responsibility - your keys, your coins, your responsibility.' },
        { title: 'custodial', description: 'while they may seem convenient, remember: if you don\'t control the keys, you don\'t truly own the bitcoin. this model reintroduces the very trust issues bitcoin was designed to solve.' }
    ]
};
---
<section class="bg-[#FFBF78] min-h-screen p-4 flex flex-col items-center justify-center ">
    <h1 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mt-4 md:mt-10 text-center text-gray-800 sm:mt-5">bitcoin, a real digital wallet</h1>
    <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl md:text-2xl mb-6 mt-2 text-center text-gray-800">don't get lost in the jargon of categorization</h3>
    <div class="w-full max-w-6xl mx-auto">
        <div class="flex flex-col lg:flex-row items-center justify-center mb-8">
            <img 
                src="/oldwallet.svg" 
                alt="bitcoin wallet conceptual illustration" 
                class="w-1/2 md:w-1/3 lg:w-1/4 h-auto object-contain mb-6 lg:mb-0"
            />
            
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4 w-full lg:w-3/4 lg:ml-4">
                {Object.entries(categories).map(([category, items]) => (
                    <div class="bg-[#FFEEA9] p-4 rounded-lg shadow-lg">
                        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">by {category}</h2>
                        <ul class="text-xs sm:text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-2">
                            {items.map((item) => (
                                <li><strong>{item.title}:</strong> {item.description}</li>
                            ))}
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                ))}
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-gray-700 mt-4 text-center max-w-2xl">
        not every wallet is created equal. pro-tip: when choosing a wallet, always keep in mind decentralization and individual sovereignty.
    </p>
</section>